FaultDescription: A stuck transaction in CBo TOR. The Cbo Table of Request (TOR) timer has expired on a transaction. This means that the transaction did not complete in the allocated time. The Status Registers have fields for valid MISC and Valid Address. If these fields are valid MISC and ADDR bank register values should be decoded. The transaction address and type are encoded in those registers. The MISC register will log the: Core ID, Thread ID, Cacheability, Original Request and Opcode. The Original Request field should be used to note the request type. The ADDR register contains the target physical address cacheline aligned.
FaultAction: CPU1: Verify system have latest microcode; Decode CHA MCA Banks, if TOR Dump available use TOR Dump to identify blocked transactions and FSM, decode address; Monitor Failure Rate for 3 months, On repeated error same CPUx/CHA contact OEM debug team; contact your Intel representative.
